    The current state of a transfer. A transfer is initially in WAITING state when added. It will turn into IN_PROGRESS once it starts. Customers can pause or cancel the transfer when needed and turns it into PAUSED or CANCELED state respectively. Finally the transfer will either succeed as COMPLETED or fail as FAILED. WAITING_FOR_NETWORK state may kick in for an active transfer when network is lost. The other enum values are internal use only.
